quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  82,1,When the heaven developed cracks
  82,2,and when the planets slipped hither and thither
  82,3,and when the seas are burst forth (overriding their invisible barriers)
  82,4,and when the graves are exhumed (of their contents)
  82,5,"(Afterwards, during Accountability) a Nafs came to know what she has sent forward (as her deeds) and what she left behind (as her traditions at the time she left the world)"
  82,6,O you the human! What has made you careless concerning your Most Generous Nourisher-Sustainer —
  82,7,"Who created you, then fashioned you in perfection, then He set you in due proportion"
  82,8,"In whatever form, that He desired, He developed you in shape"
  82,9,"Nay! Of course, you deny Accountability and Judgment"
  82,10,"And certainly, over you, (are) indeed (set) guards and protectors"
  82,11,Kiraman Katibin (Honourable scribes)
  82,12,They know whatever you do (and they immediately record your deeds)
  82,13,"Verily, Al-Abrar (will be) indeed in delights (of Paradise)"
  82,14,"And verily, Al-Fujjar (will be) indeed in blazing Fire (of Hell)"
  82,15,they will reach therein on the Day of Judgment
  82,16,"and they (i.e., Al-Fujjar) will not be absent therefrom"
  82,17,And what did make you know what the Day of Judgment (is)
  82,18,Once more! What did make you know what the Day of Judgment or Recompense is
  82,19,"The Day a Nafs does not own anything to favour or assist or redeem any Nafs. And the matter, that Day is solely with Allah"
  83,1,Woe to the fraudulents
  83,2,"those who when they took by measure from other people, will take (it) full"
  83,3,"and when they gave by measure to others, or weighed for others — they deduct and give less by weight and measure"
  83,4,"Don't such people realise that they (one day, would be) those who have been resurrected (into a new life and have to face Accountability)"
  83,5,in relation to a Great Day —
  83,6,the Day (all) mankind stands before (the) Nourisher-Sustainer of the worlds